## Third-Party Sources

The following source texts are included or referenced with their respective permissions:

### GRETIL (Göttingen Register of Electronic Texts in Indian Languages)
Sanskrit texts from GRETIL are used under their terms of scholarly use.
http://gretil.sub.uni-goettingen.de/

### CBETA (Chinese Buddhist Electronic Text Association)
Chinese Buddhist texts from CBETA are used under their open access terms.
https://www.cbeta.org/

### 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha
Tibetan texts referenced follow 84000's licensing for scholarly use.
https://84000.co/

### Taishō Tripiṭaka
The Taishō Shinshū Daizōkyō is in the public domain.

## Academic Citation

When citing this edition:

```
Zigmond, Dan et al. (2026). Heart Sūtra Critical Edition.
Electronic multilingual critical edition with Chinese compositional priority.
https://github.com/[repository-url]
```

